---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FlowOP | Operational Clarity as a Service"
  description="Operations Alignment Sprint for growing product and distribution businesses. Bring reporting, planning, and execution back into sync in 10 business days."
  pathname="/"
>
  <main class="home-page">
    <section class="hero-home">
      <div class="hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="container hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-grid">
          <div class="hero-copy">
            <span class="hero-eyebrow reveal">Systems builder support · growing teams</span>
            <h1 class="hero-title reveal">
              When growth<br />
              outpaces<br />
              <em class="hero-title-accent">your systems.</em>
            </h1>
            <p class="hero-lead reveal">
              The Operations Alignment Sprint reconnects reporting, planning, and execution in <strong
                >10 business days</strong
              > — scoped, practical, and built to hand over cleanly.
            </p>
            <div class="hero-actions reveal">
              <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Book Discovery Call</a>
              <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">View Services</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-panel-glow">
            <aside class="hero-panel reveal">
              <h3 class="hero-panel-title">Outcomes teams notice first</h3>
              <ul class="hero-panel-list">
                <li>Reporting and decisions move on a reliable weekly rhythm.</li>
                <li>Planning and handoffs feel coordinated, not reactive.</li>
                <li>An operating layer your team trusts and runs independently.</li>
              </ul>
            </aside>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="hero-tagline-bar">
      <div class="container hero-tagline-row">
        <p class="hero-tagline">
          <span class="hero-tagline-serif">Your </span><span class="hero-tagline-accent">Silent Partner</span><span
            class="hero-tagline-serif"> in Performance.</span>
        </p>
        <span class="hero-tagline-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <p class="hero-trust-pill" role="note">
          <span class="hero-trust-pill-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="hero-trust-pill-text">
            Scoped engagements <span class="hero-trust-mid" aria-hidden="true">·</span> Clear deliverables <span
              class="hero-trust-mid" aria-hidden="true">·</span> No ongoing dependency
          </span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="why-flowop">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="why-kicker reveal">— Why <span class="brand-mark">FlowOP</span></p>
        <div class="why-grid">
          <div class="why-col-left">
            <h2 class="why-title reveal">
              Practical systems support before you need a full <br /><em class="why-title-accent">ops department.</em>
            </h2>
            <p class="why-intro reveal">
              Growing businesses hit a point where execution outpaces their ability to manage it. FlowOP exists to fill
              that gap — without the overhead of a full-time hire.
            </p>
            <div class="why-stat reveal">
              <span class="why-stat-num" aria-hidden="true">20+</span>
              <div class="why-stat-copy">
                <strong>Years of hands-on experience</strong>
                <span>Planning, supply chain, logistics, reporting &amp; operational finance.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ol class="why-rows why-col-right">
            <li class="why-row reveal">
              <span class="why-num">01</span>
              <div class="why-row-body">
                <h3>Fractional, not full-time</h3>
                <p>
                  One dedicated day per week. Right-sized for growing teams who need real expertise without a full
                  headcount.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="why-row reveal">
              <span class="why-num">02</span>
              <div class="why-row-body">
                <h3>Deliverables, not dependency</h3>
                <p>
                  Every sprint ends with assets your team owns and can run independently — no ongoing retainer required.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="why-row reveal">
              <span class="why-num">03</span>
              <div class="why-row-body">
                <h3>Clarity before scale</h3>
                <p>
                  Alignment comes before investment. Start with a sprint, then decide what to build next based on what
                  you actually need.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="why-row reveal">
              <span class="why-num">04</span>
              <div class="why-row-body">
                <h3>Remote-first, milestone-driven</h3>
                <p>
                  Most work is remote. On-site visits are planned in advance around key milestones — not billed by default.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sprint-section">
      <div class="container">
        <header class="sprint-header reveal">
          <p class="sprint-kicker rule-kicker">Flagship engagement</p>
          <h2 class="sprint-title">Operations Alignment Sprint</h2>
          <p class="sprint-sub">
            Ten focused business days: identify where reporting, planning, and execution drift — then fix it, hand it
            over, and leave your team with clear ownership.
          </p>
        </header>

        <div class="sprint-board reveal">
          <div class="sprint-board-inner">
            <article class="sprint-col">
              <div class="sprint-col-head">
                <div class="sprint-step-num">01</div>
                <span class="sprint-days">Days 1–3</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="sprint-phase">Understand</h3>
              <p class="sprint-step-text">
                Map where reporting, planning, and execution are drifting apart. Identify the highest-impact friction
                points.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="sprint-col">
              <div class="sprint-col-head">
                <div class="sprint-step-num">02</div>
                <span class="sprint-days">Days 4–8</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="sprint-phase">Realign</h3>
              <p class="sprint-step-text">
                Implement practical fixes that improve decision flow and day-to-day coordination across teams.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="sprint-col sprint-col--last">
              <div class="sprint-col-head">
                <div class="sprint-step-num">03</div>
                <span class="sprint-days">Days 9–10</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="sprint-phase">Transition</h3>
              <p class="sprint-step-text">
                Hand over clear ownership, operating guidance, and a roadmap for the next stage of growth.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sprint-deliver reveal">
          <span class="sprint-deliver-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          <p>
            <strong>You leave with three practical assets:</strong> a decision-ready operating map, updated workflows
            with clear ownership, and a weekly cadence your team can run without ongoing dependency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-section">
      <div class="container case-layout">
        <div class="case-intro">
          <p class="case-kicker rule-kicker-light reveal">Example engagement</p>
          <h2 class="case-title reveal">What an alignment sprint looks like in practice.</h2>
          <p class="case-lead reveal">
            A real-world example of how a focused sprint restores operational clarity for a growing team.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-panel reveal">
          <div class="case-band">
            <span class="case-badge case-badge--situation">Situation</span>
            <p>
              A growing team was making weekly decisions with <strong>delayed reporting and reactive planning.</strong> Reports
              were fragmented across functions, handoffs were inconsistent, and leadership had no single operating view to
              act from.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="case-band">
            <span class="case-badge case-badge--intervention">Intervention</span>
            <p>
              In a focused 10-day sprint: <strong>rebuilt the reporting cadence</strong> so leadership worked from one
              consistent view, clarified cross-team handoffs with clear ownership, and introduced a practical planning rhythm
              the team could maintain independently.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="case-band case-band--last">
            <span class="case-badge case-badge--result">Result</span>
            <p>
              <strong>Faster weekly decisions, fewer escalation loops, and clearer ownership</strong> across functions —
              handed over with practical guidance the team ran without ongoing support.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="services-section">
      <div class="container">
        <header class="services-header reveal">
          <p class="services-kicker rule-kicker">Ways to engage</p>
          <h2 class="services-title">Start with alignment, scale support as needed.</h2>
        </header>
        <div class="services-grid">
          <article class="services-card reveal">
            <span class="services-tag">Core offer</span>
            <h3>Operations Alignment Sprint</h3>
            <p>Best when teams need to restore clarity quickly and regain control over execution.</p>
            <ul class="services-list">
              <li>Reporting, planning, and workflow misalignment</li>
              <li>10 business days with clear transition ownership</li>
              <li>Smoother execution and decision confidence</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="services-card reveal">
            <span class="services-tag">Extended support</span>
            <h3>Systems Buildout</h3>
            <p>Best when teams need deeper redesign across structures, tools, and operating routines.</p>
            <ul class="services-list">
              <li>Businesses outgrowing patchwork processes</li>
              <li>Multi-track design and implementation work</li>
              <li>Coordinated systems for sustainable growth</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="services-card reveal">
            <span class="services-tag">Ongoing partnership</span>
            <h3>Ongoing Operational Support</h3>
            <p>Best for teams needing steady operational guidance through ongoing growth cycles.</p>
            <ul class="services-list">
              <li>Recurring friction across teams and functions</li>
              <li>Cadence support, refinement, and coaching</li>
              <li>Stable execution as complexity increases</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
        <div class="services-cta-bar reveal">
          <p>
            Book a discovery call to scope the right first sprint — start with alignment, then decide the next step
            together.
          </p>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Book Discovery Call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pain-section">
      <div class="container pain-inner">
        <header class="pain-header reveal">
          <p class="pain-kicker rule-kicker">If this feels familiar</p>
          <h2 class="pain-title">Your team may be ready for an alignment sprint.</h2>
          <p class="pain-intro">
            Growth often arrives before systems are ready. Clarity first — then confidence in execution.
          </p>
        </header>
        <ul class="pain-list">
          <li class="pain-item reveal">
            <span class="pain-item-label">Reporting delays:</span>
            Weekly decisions slow because reports are late, fragmented, or hard to rely on.
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item reveal">
            <span class="pain-item-label">Planning strain:</span>
            Demand, capacity, and inventory planning feels reactive instead of coordinated.
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item reveal">
            <span class="pain-item-label">Execution friction:</span>
            Too much time on handoffs, chasing updates, and reworking tasks.
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item reveal">
            <span class="pain-item-label">Disconnected systems:</span>
            Tools and workflows no longer fit how the business actually operates.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-banner" aria-labelledby="cta-banner-heading">
      <div class="container cta-banner-inner">
        <h2 id="cta-banner-heading" class="cta-banner-title reveal">
          Ready to align<br />
          <em class="cta-banner-accent">operations first?</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="cta-banner-lead reveal">
          Book a discovery call to scope the right first sprint. Start with alignment — then decide the next step
          together.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary cta-banner-btn reveal" href="/contact">Book Discovery Call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
